// useSessionPolling
// Polls /api/session-state at a regular interval as a fallback for missed WebSocket updates.

Polling is skipped when project or session are null.
Updates are applied only when lastActivity has changed, avoiding unnecessary re-renders.
Network errors are silently swallowed — polling continues on the next interval regardless.

FUNCTION useSessionPolling(project, session, intervalMs)                        EXPORT
  CALLS: useSessionStore (sessionStore)
  On mount (when project and session are set), performs an initial fetch then repeats at intervalMs (default 5000ms).
  Compares the fetched lastActivity against the current collabState.lastActivity via a ref to avoid stale closures.
  IF state has changed, updates collabState in the store.
  On unmount or dependency change, clears the interval.

---

FUNCTION poll()
  Fetches /api/session-state for the current project and session.
  IF the response's lastActivity differs from the last known value, updates collabState in the store.
  Silently ignores non-ok responses and network errors.
